constitutional amendments in the last three years have increased 
the time police may hold suspects without charge from 48 hours to 
14 days and removed security of tenure from judges and government 
auditors making them susceptible to political pressure 
they have gone toward establishing a totalitarian dictatorial 
system of government said gitobu imanyara a prominent lawyer 
and editor of the nairobi law monthly 
