very serious in their neighborhoods 35 percent to 17 percent 
and blacks were far more likely than whites to say they personally 
know someone who uses cocaine 52 percent to 31 percent 
the survey also found stark evidence of the addictive power of 
cocaine or its smokable derivative crack of the respondents who 
knew a cocaine user half said they believed the user was addicted 
that means one in six american adults personally knows a suspected 
cocaine addict 
the new poll was conducted by telephone may 1120 among a random 
sample of 1143 adults it had a margin of error of plus or minus 3 
percentage points 
