officials had consulted with philippine officials on security 
gomez was asked monday whether given reports that swanson was 
friendly with the rebels the volunteer might have gone with them 
freely 
he said that was speculative but added of course the 
telltale marks are there he did not elaborate 
swansons father leonard said his son knew rebels in the area 
but that he never considered them a threat 
he tried to be friendly with all the folks in the village and 
all who he encountered swansons father said in an interview in 
cheyenne 
