nasa engineers said today they must find and 
quickly fix a hydrogen leak that has grounded the space shuttle 
fleet or the agency will have to postpone still more shuttle 
missions 
space shuttle chief william lenoir said it was still not known 
what caused a hydrogen leak in two of the nations three space 
shuttles but he said the problem must be fixed within a few weeks 
to keep nasa anywhere near its ambitious flight schedule 
columbia was to have been launched in may on an astronomy 
mission the schedule called for other launches by atlantis in 
july columbia again in august and then discovery in october 
a leak in columbias hydrogen system in may and the discovery 
last week of a similar leak on atlantis scrambled that nasa launch 
schedule and lenoir said it is unclear now if the agency can 
recover in time to fly all the missions this year 
discoverys flight cannot be changed because its cargo is the 
ulysses science probe that is to study the sun the craft must be 
launched during a planetary alignment that occurs only once in 
every two years 
were right on the edge of the point where two flights no 
longer fit in the schedule before the launch of ulysses said 
lenoir fixing the leak he said will have to be quick and simple 
to avoid more changes in the nasa launch schedule 
parts of columbia are being tested in a laboratory and lenoir 
said that atlantis may again be tested on the launch pad at the 
kennedy space center in florida the engineers he said should 
have more answers by thursday 
meanwhile an investigation should start formally later this 
week on why the hubble space telescope was launched with a flawed 
focusing system 
engineers testing the orbiting space telescope found last week 
that either the primary or the secondary mirrors on the 15 
billion telescope were flawed so badly that starlight could not be 
focused as precisely as had been planned the poor focus seriously 
affects how well the telescope can study the universe 
nasa chief scientist lennard fisk said that scientists are 
working to determine how the unfocused light can be manipulated by 
computer to give clear pictures of the distant stars 
there are two characteristics of the people who work for nasa 
were stubborn and were clever said fisk were going to make 
this thing work 
fisk said that the agency will complete the appointment of an 
investigation committee this week he said the investigation would 
review the entire history of hubble and should find answers for why 
the mirrors are flawed 
