platform which calls for abandoning the 70year experiment 
with communism and opting for west european style social democracy 
one member of the democratic platform grigory omelchenko of 
kiev wearing a redandwhite dp button on his lapel said he 
did not want reformers to split from the party for the time being 
he said he wanted to prevent a coalition of centrist and hardline 
forces 
but arguing is only natural protested ivan polozkov an extreme 
conservative 
we are on our way to political pluralism said polozkov 
whose election as head of the russian branch of the party last 
momth strengthened predictions of a party split 
just nine minutes into the meeting a coal miner stood to call 
for the resignation of the top 250 leaders in the party including 
gorbachev for failure to improve the countrys standard of living 
but gorbachev swept it off the floor with the promise of a 
discussion later in the 10day meeting 
during gorbachevs 2 hour 20minute speech applause was rare 
and very light 
but delegates clapped long and hard for alexander yakovlev a 
leading reformer disliked by the hardliners 
yakovlev followed party ideologue vadim a medvedev to the 
podium medvedev had been jeered 
im also in for a tough few minutes yakovlev deadpanned 
drawing laugher from the conservative crowd 
yakovlev won the attention and apparently the respect of the 
delegates with his blunt uncompromising support for gorbachevs 
reforms and condemnation of the partys history 
in contrast to the soviet parliament where some delegates wear 
flowered headscarves flowing clerical robes and the square 
embroidered caps of central asia the party congress was nearly 
colorless a sea of graysuited managers and bureaucrats 
women were rare as were the workers and peasants the communist 
party claims to represent after party apparatchiks engineered 
their own election to nearly half the seats at the congress 
officials discovered that fewer than 7 percent of the delegates 
were factory workers and farmers so they invited 300 as guests 
