a peace corps volunteer kidnapped by 
rebels in the philippines was described as a brilliant but shy 
young man by acquaintances in his hometown 
timothy swanson 26 was abducted june 13 by members of the new 
peoples army from the island of negros where he was working as a 
volunteer for the peace corps 
swanson grew up and attended public school in cheyenne 
tim was a very bright student said walt miner an english 
teacher at cheyenne east high school where swanson graduated in 
1982 he was very precise and he was quite a good student 
hes a brilliant young man kind of shy but intelligent 
said the rev eugene todd of st marks episcopal church where 
swanson served as an altar boy to go to the philippines and do 
what he was doing seemed perfectly natural 
swanson a national merit scholar did not take part in sports 
in school but focused instead on academics said his father 
leonard swanson 
swanson did not participate much in group activities miner 
said although he added that he never considered swanson a loner 
after graduating from cheyenne east swanson attended the 
university of chicago where he studied geography 
leonard swanson said tim became interested in joining the peace 
corps in 1987 
he decided to go into the peace corps for basically 
humanitarian reasons he said he felt a need to try to help 
some folks who he thought might be in need 
swanson went to the philippines in february 1988 he recently 
completed his twoyear assignment but obtained a 13month 
extension 
he was married to a filipino teacher on may 29 
swanson enjoyed his work in the philippines which involved a 
reforestation project his father said he added that he believes 
his son has the qualities needed to weather the abduction 
i think he has the personality and the patience the 
perception to handle this in a satisfactory manner he said 
