a mentally retarded man went on trial 
for a second time monday in the 1979 stabbing death of a 
22yearold woman a crime for which he was nearly executed four 
years ago 
prosecutors told jurors that death row inmate johnny paul penry 
had nearly stomped the victim to death before calmly stabbing 
her with a pair of scissors 
defense attorneys said penrys retardation was at the root of 
the case 
penry now 34 has been on death row since 1980 when a jury 
convicted him of capital murder in the death of pamela moseley 
carpenter mrs carpenter was the sister of former washington 
redskins kicker mark moseley 
in 1986 he came within hours of execution by lethal injection 
before receiving a stay from the us supreme court the court 
vacated his death sentence two years ago saying jurors should have 
been told about penrys retardation 
prosecutors are retrying the entire case because under texas 
law in a capital murder case the penalty phase alone cannot be 
retried 
in opening arguments monday district attorney joe price 
described how penry allegedly forced his way into mrs carpenters 
home the morning of oct 25 1979 and how she was attacked 
he dragged her knocked her down into the bedroom price 
said he nearly stomped the life out of her stomped her into 
submission then he calmly and deliberately walked across the room 
picked up a pair of orangehandled scissors sat on her stomach 
looked her in the eye and stabbed her in the chest 
you will never for the rest of your lives forget these 
orangehandled scissors price told the jurors she reached up 
and pulled the scissors out of her chest 
she died within hours of the assault penry confessed in a 
signed statement after he was arrested 
in an ordinary case perhaps a signed statement would convince 
you penrys attorney john wright said of his clients 
confession to police 
this is no ordinary case johnny paul is mentally retarded 
all the horror story youve just been recounted had its start right 
there 
penry has said he was abused by his parents particularly by his 
mother and never attended regular school beyond a few days in the 
first grade because of his retardation 
he has an iq estimated at between 50 and 60 and the reasoning 
capacity of a 7yearold 
in testimony monday mrs carpenters husband bruce identified 
bloody clothing as belonging to his wife he also described his 
wife of three years as young and beautiful and then identified 
her battered body in a picture taken after her death 
penry who replied not guilty when asked monday for a plea 
sat attentively during the arguments and initial testimony at 
times he exchanged words with one of his attorneys 
penry has denied killing mrs carpenter i told them i did it 
but i didnt do it he has said i dont know who did it all i 
know is i didnt 
