dick thornburg editor of the cincinnati post 
during much of the fifties and sixties has died at age 86 
thornburg died saturday in prescott ariz where he had lived 
the cause of death was not given 
he was the consummate newspaperman said william r 
burleigh senior vice president of scripps howard and a former 
editor of the post he loved newspapers and he understood what 
the role of a newspaper was in the community 
thornburg began his journalism career in 1929 as a 1750aweek 
copy boy with the old columbus ohio citizen 
he was managing editor of the scripps howard newspaper alliance 
in washington dc before being named editor of the post in 1953 
he retired from that job in 1969 
former ohio gov james a rhodes recalled that thornburg was a 
leading advocate of building cincinnatis riverfront stadium 
downtown along the banks of the ohio river rather than in the 
suburbs the downtown advocates won and the ballpark now home of 
baseballs cincinnati reds and footballs cincinnati bengals 
opened in june 1970 
