installation of an independent electoral council on may 2 to 
organize presidential elections 
the army leadership has pledged to cooperate with the civilian 
caretaker government of president ertha pascaltrouillot in 
providing security for the coming elections but loyalists of the 
former duvalierist dictatorship both in and out of the army are 
violently opposed to a transition to democracy 
on june 28 four gunmen including two in army uniforms 
attacked a meeting of the 19member council of state and killed 
council member serge villard and union activist jeanmarie montes 
haitis last attempt to hold free and fair elections on nov 
29 1987 failed when thugs supported by the army shot and hacked 
to death at least 34 voters at polling stations 
