<DOCNO> AP900702-0166 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the hajj an annual pilgrimage to islams holiest shrines in 
saudi arabia is the worlds largest religious gathering it brings 
together arabian princes merchants from indonesia peasants from 
soviet uzbekistan and paupers from bangladesh 
the hajj must be made at least once in a lifetime by all moslems 
who can afford it performing the hajj is one of the five 
pillars of the islamic faith the others are professing that 
there is only one god and mohammed is his prophet saying the five 
daily prayers giving alms to the poor and observing the 
dawntodusk fast during the lunar month of ramadan 
a moslem who performs the pilgrimage is called a hajji each 
year hundreds of thousands of moslems from around the world travel 
to the holy city of mecca by land sea or even on foot for the 
pilgrimage 
the pilgrims join in chanting god is so great and to him we 
pay high tribute waves of veiled women and men in white seamless 
robes signifying equality before allah take part in the prayers 
during the hajj pilgrims must abstain from sex and may not 
quarrel cut their hair or even kill a fly 
the hajj is performed during the islamic lunar months of 
shawwal zul quideh and zulhijjeh similar rituals performed out 
of the season are called umrah or lesser hajj 
the hajj proper is limited to six days a pilgrim may commence 
the rituals at any time during the three months 
hajjis start the pilgrimage by praying at the grand mosque in 
mecca they then circle seven times around the kaaba a granite 
cube draped with goldembroidered black brocade moslems honor the 
kaaba as the house of allah where the prophet abraham offered his 
first prayers to god 
as they circle the cube pilgrims bend to kiss the sacred black 
stone set in silver on the east corner of the granite structure 
moslems believe the stone is a meteorite which came from heaven 
the legend says the stone was originally white but became black 
over the centuries as hajjis washed away their sins on it 
hajjis are then required to run back and forth seven times 
between two rocks about halfamile apart called alsafa and 
almarwa this ceremony is meant to relive the agony of hagar 
abrahams second wife when she was looking for water for her son 
ishmael considered the ancestor of the arabs 
the main center of the pilgrimage then moves to mina a meeting 
place for the hajjis to gather before they climb mount arafat for 
the climax of the observances moslems believe arafat is where 
abraham showed his devotion to god by offering to sacrifice his son 
at mount arafat each pilgrim throws seven stones at each of the 
three devil pillars a spot where moslems believe the devil 
tried to tempt abraham to disobey allah and refuse to sacrifice his 
son 
at twilight pilgrims offer the eid aladha or feast of 
sacrifice prayers before slaughtering hundreds of thousands of 
sheep cows and camels 
the meat traditionally goes to poor saudis but since the 
discovery of oil virtually eliminated poverty in the kingdom most 
is flown to poor moslems in 26 countries 
hundreds of thousands of pilgrims then stream down mount arafat 
to the mina plain and on to mecca for the farewell prayer before 
dispersing creating what may be the worlds biggest traffic jam 
arafat is about eight miles from mecca 
it is at this stage that most accidents occur 
the saudi government has spent 15 billion in recent years on a 
development plan to move pilgrims in a more orderly fashion for the 
hajj building networks of roads tunnels dormitories and medical 
clinics the tunnel where mondays tragedy occurred is one of 
several equipped with giant ventilators and air conditioning 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900702-0167 </DOCNO>
