despite a lack of enthusiasm for his 2hour 20minute speech 
opening the communist partys crucial 28th congress the soviet 
leader appeared to have papered over differences between reformers 
and traditionalists with equal doses of confrontation conciliation 
and confession 
applause was rare and very light during his speech 
delegates displayed little strong emotion despite declarations 
by the party leader that the congress would decide the communist 
partys fate 
