<TEXT>
a new law requires largecirculation 
newspapers printed or sold in suffolk county to start using 
recycled paper at the end of next year 
the law requires a complete switch to recycled paper for 
newspapers with weekly circulations of 20000 or more by the end of 
1996 
county executive patrick halpin who signed the measure on june 
29 said it would help solve long islands garbage crisis by 
creating a market for recycled newspapers 
i hope this law spurs the state and federal government to 
adopt similar legislation because communities are drowning in 
their garbage he said 
all the large daily newspapers sold in the county will be 
affected including newsday the new york times the new york post 
the daily news and usa today 
the law will take effect dec 31 1991 under a timetable that 
will allow the papers to gradually shift to recycling by the end of 
1996 
</TEXT>
