datatimes and dow jones information 
services have agreed to a joint marketing and service deal to 
combine their electronic libraries the two companies anounced 
monday 
the arrangement will allow researchers to search electronically 
through the computerized files of 640 newspapers magazines news 
services and financial data sources more than 450 sources will be 
available for simultaneous access 
