of up to 15 billion should initially result in a sharp 
deterioration in the capital structure of mci and correspondingly 
higher fixed charges sampp said 
however the merger strengthens mcis position in the rapidly 
growing and profitable smallbusiness phone market it said 
sampp said mci should pay off the acquisitionrelated debt by the 
end of 1993 due to its ability to generate robust cash flow 
mci the nations no 2 longdistance carrier after american 
telephone amp telegraph co announced the merger with atlantabased 
telecom in april 
