<TEXT>
crude oil prices dropped in light trading 
monday weakened by word that norways government had moved to end 
a petroleum workers strike but wholesale gasoline prices rose 
slightly because of seasonal driving demand 
on the new york mercantile exchange the august contract for key 
west texas intermediate crude fell 35 cents a barrel to 1672 
subsequent contract months also fell 
brokers attributed the decline largely to developments in the 
dayold norway oil workers walkout which had halted the countrys 
production of 163 million barrels of oil per day 
the strike at first raised speculation of a supply shortage that 
would drive up world prices temporarily and buyers jumped in to 
profit from that possibility 
but when the government issued a backtowork decree and a 
bindingarbitration order the supplyshortage theory was 
discounted and oilmarket speculators drove crude prices back down 
the drop in crude spilled over into the homeheating oil market 
on the new york mercantile exchange wholesale homeheating oil for 
august delivery fell 06 cent per gallon to 4856 cents 
latermonth contracts also fell 
among other refined products traded on the exchange unleaded 
gasoline for august delivery rose 047 cent a gallon to 5668 
cents largely because of what brokers called higher demand for 
gasoline in the summer later contract months were lower 
in natural gas trading the august contract was unchanged at 
1519 per 1000 cubic feet 
