<TEXT>
a rhode island securities firm was expelled 
and one of its principals fined 15 million by the national 
association of securities dealers on monday 
the nasd a selfregulating organization that oversees the 
overthecounter securities market said brandon securities amp 
investments and ernest e michaud a registered principal of the 
north providence firm settled fraud accusations without admitting 
or denying wrongdoing 
the nasd accused brandon of engaging in a scheme to defraud 20 
investors of 15 million over a fouryear period by promoting and 
selling shares in an investment pool and then either misapplying or 
stealing the money outright 
an investigation by the nasds district 13 committee in boston 
alleged that brandon 42 of kingston ri also supplied 
customers with fictitious statements that contained false 
representations about their investors 
the investors were not identified 
according to the nasd the firm was expelled from membership in 
the association and in addition to the fine he agreed to pay 
michaud is barred from association with any nasd in any business 
capacity 
in other disciplinary actions announced monday the nasd 
expelled a tiburon calif firm baldwin capital partners from 
membership and fined a principal george horace baldwin also of 
tiburon 5000 for failing to respond to nasd requests for 
information 
fined a rolling meadows ill firm dmartine financial 
services inc 50000 for failing to maintain required minimum net 
capital and filing inaccurate reports 
